  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "[Writing `value` into the final `textarea` html](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/a8fc3b940dbe20c0c7decd19b028215b236c50a6/src/browser/ui/dom/components/ReactDOMTextarea.js#L112) creates invalid html markup and appears to be unnecessary for proper functionality of the `ReactDOMTextarea`.\n\nAdmittedly my test here was very minimal, but removing `value` from the `props` object using `delete props.value;` rendered valid html and the component still worked properly in the browser and passed all it's tests.\n\nOther than perhaps supporting server-side rendering, is there a purpose to rendering `value` into the real dom?\n",
